          %h1.marker
            Agile Poker
%section(style="border-top:1px solid #e0e0e0")
  .row
    .col-md-2
    .col-md-5
      .row
        .col-md-12
          %p
            This
            %a(href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planning_poker' target='_blank') collaborative task estimation
            tool provides a space for developers to discuss, vote, and reach consensus on the complexity of a task.

          %h4.marker
            Getting Started
          
          %h6.marker
            Lobby

          %p
            %ul
              %i.fa.fa-user
                Choose a username
              %br
              %i.fa.fa-sign-in
                Sign into the lobby
              %br
              %i.fa.fa-comments-o
                Chat in the lobby
              %br
              %i.fa.fa-sign-in
                Create or enter a planning room
              %br
          
          %h6.marker
            Planning Rooms
          %p
            %ul
              %i.fa.fa-gear
                Assign an admin
              %br
              %i.fa.fa-comments-o
                Discuss the task
              %br
              %i.fa.fa-pencil
                Vote on the complexity of the task
              %br
              %i.fa.fa-bar-chart-o
                Reveal the voting consensus
          %br
          %h6.marker
            Visual Demo
            %br
            %img(src='images/out.gif')
          %br
          %h6.marker
            Text Demo
            %div.chat-example
              [Leader]: The next task under discussion is WIDGET-193, adding a 'like' button to the widget interface
              %br
              %br
              [Developer A]: Does this include the 'like' frontend and backend?
              %br 
              %br
              [Leader]: Yes - good clarification. Any other questions?
              %br 
              %br
              [Developers A, B, C, D]: Nope. All set!
              %br 
              %br
              [Leader]: OK, let's vote.
              %br 
              %br
              [Developers D, B, C, A]: /cast hidden votes/
              %br 
              %br
              [Leader]: Ok, revealing the vote!
              %br 
              %br
              (The vote is A:10, B:10, C:8, D:13)
              %br 
              %br
              [Leader]: Looks like we have a consensus value of 10. Developers C and D, are you in agreement with that?
              %br 
              %br
              (Developers C and D have a chance to explain)
              %br 
              %br
              [Leader]: OK, looks like this is a 10. On to the next task!
              %br
              %br
              (The leader could also reset the vote and start over)
          

           
